Feature: Profile picture upload with OpenCV JNI

Contract IDs
- `CID-LOGIN-PROFILE-UPLOAD`
- `CID-MBOOK-PROFILEPICTURE-UPDATE`

Overview
- Add authenticated profile picture upload/change capability.
- Initial client scope: iOS `MenuVC` only.
- Upload path uses existing dalogin auth model (Option A).
- Image processing uses OpenCV through JNI integrated in backend runtime.

Role collaboration
- `@backend-dev`, `@cpp-developer`, `@database-dev`, `@security-specialist`, `@ios-dev`, `@devops`, `@testing-engineer`

Functional requirements
- `FR-000`: C++ image-resizing app update is a hard prerequisite and MUST be completed before backend JNI upload integration.
- `FR-001`: System MUST expose `POST /login/profile-picture` protected by session/XSRF/HMAC.
- `FR-002`: `dalogin` MUST proxy upload payload to `mbook` without bypassing auth checks.
- `FR-003`: `mbook` MUST resize the uploaded image through JNI/OpenCV before persisting.
- `FR-003A`: JNI/OpenCV resize API MUST accept backend arguments: `targetWidth`, `targetHeight`, `maxBytes`, `canCrop`, `keepAspectRatio`.
- `FR-003B`: `maxBytes` MUST be treated as a precise upper limit for output size.
- `FR-003C`: `canCrop` and `keepAspectRatio` behavior MUST be deterministic and documented for conflicting combinations.
- `FR-004`: Final file MUST be stored on PVC path `/pictures/profiles`.
- `FR-005`: `mbook` MUST update `Logins.profilePicture` only after successful file write.
- `FR-006`: Response MUST return updated `profilePicture` path for immediate client refresh.
- `FR-007`: Allowed upload formats MUST be validated (jpg/jpeg/png), oversized files rejected.
- `FR-008`: Filenames MUST be sanitized and generated server-side (no trust in client filename).
- `FR-009`: Existing `GET /rest/user/{user}/{token1}` response MUST continue returning `profilePicture`.

Security requirements
- `SEC-001`: Upload endpoint MUST require valid authenticated session and XSRF cookie.
- `SEC-002`: MIME type and extension checks MUST be enforced before processing.
- `SEC-003`: Path traversal attempts MUST be rejected.
- `SEC-004`: Error payloads MUST avoid leaking internal filesystem/native details.

Non-functional requirements
- `NFR-001`: Resize operation should complete under 1s for typical profile image sizes.
- `NFR-002`: PVC write failures MUST return explicit recoverable error status.
- `NFR-003`: Native library load failures MUST produce controlled API error and logs.

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] iOS `MenuVC` can upload/change profile picture through `dalogin`.
- [ ] Stored image exists under `/pictures/profiles` and is served by image service.
- [ ] `logins.profilePicture` is updated in `mbook` DB path only.
- [ ] Invalid file types/sizes are rejected with 4xx.
- [ ] JNI resize path is validated in container runtime.

Definition of Done
- [ ] Feature has spec, implementation, and tests.
- [ ] `@testing-engineer` verification done.
- [ ] `@security-specialist` verification done.
- [ ] `@performance-engineer` verification done.
- [ ] Contract IDs are registered/updated in `.github/references/CONTRACTS_INDEX.md`.

